&lt;h2&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Descriptors are one of the most powerful features of Python. The reason why
they're so powerful is because they enable us to control the core operations
(get, set, delete) &lt;a class="footnote-reference" href="https://rmariano.github.io/itarch/posts/a-first-look-at-descriptors.html#id5" id="id1"&gt;[1]&lt;/a&gt;, of an attribute in a given object, so that we can hook
a particular code, controlled by us, in order to modify, change, or extend the
original operation.&lt;/p&gt;
